This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection and appearance-based detectors. It may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it explores the optimization problem of using contextual relations to improve detection scores. The paper also mentions natural language processing (cs.CL) as a potential application of their approach. Finally, the paper discusses false detections, which may fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
